1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE
----------------------
Ensure the following files are in the same working directory:
- main.py        (The Kivy GUI wrapper)
- trailer.sh     (The DERS-Patched logic engine)
- buildozer.spec (The deployment configuration)

2. COMPILATION COMMANDS
-----------------------
Initialize the environment (if not already done):
$ buildozer init

Standard Production Build (Debug APK for initial extraction):
$ buildozer -v android debug

Clean Build (Use if permissions or NDK paths shift):
$ buildozer android clean
$ buildozer -v android debug

3. TARGET SPECIFICS (Samsung A05s / SDK 35)
-------------------------------------------
Reggie requires Scoped Storage access to write to /Documents/.
After installation, you must manually grant "All Files Access" if 
the OS prompts, as Reggie performs deep-read operations on /proc/self/maps.

4. EXTRA FLAGS & OPTIMIZATIONS
------------------------------
To bypass the standard Buildozer virtualenv and force a specific NDK 
path (if using a custom toolchain):
$ P4A_ndk_directory=/path/to/ndk-r25b buildozer android debug

To see real-time execution logs and "Bino" extraction errors:
$ adb logcat -s python

5. THE "ICON TRIGGER" LOGIC
---------------------------
- Pressing the App Icon initializes the Python VM.
- The UI immediately spawns the Threaded Subprocess.
- Logic: [SCOPE] -> [SCAN] -> [SCRUB] -> [SCORE] -> [SEAL].
- Artifacts are saved to: /storage/emulated/0/Documents/ReggieAudit/

6. DEV MODE / CUSTOM BINARIES
-----------------------------
To upload custom bino-tools for Reggie to check:
1. Place the binary in the source folder.
2. Add the filename to 'source.include_exts' in buildozer.spec.
3. Update trailer.sh to point to the internal bundled path: 
   ./ext/your_binary

